obo:ECO_0006042  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_5217  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3d: MARK1 and PSD95 (DLG4) were enriched in PSD biochemical fractions from 1-month-old mouse brains.\n\nFigure 3: MARK1 phosphorylates DIXDC1 at serine 592/381 and co-localized with DIXDC1 in dendrites of cultured cortical neurons.\n\nFigure 6B: \"Expression of hDIXDC1-V43M and -T612M in HEK293 cells results in a decrease in phosphorylation at DIXDC1 serine592 in the presence of MARK1\"\n\nFigure 4, S4B: Phosphorylation of DIXDC1 isoforms by MARK1 regulates neuronal morphology.\n\"We also examined whether phosphorylation of DIXDC1 was important for its localization in dendrites and spines. Cultured cortical neurons showed co-localization of GFP-tagged hDIXDC1-WT (isoforms 1 and 2) with PSD95 in the dendritic spines (Figures 4G and 4H). However, the hDIXDC1-S592A and -S381A phospho-mutants both exhibited a decrease in PSD95 co-localization, indicating DIXDC1 localization to spines was disrupted (Figures 4G and 4H). These results strongly indicate that phosphorylation of both DIXDC1 isoforms is critical for cortical dendrite and synapse formation.\". Experimental description: M&M: \"The Dixdc1 KO mouse was generated by the Knockout Mouse Phenotyping Consortium.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-03" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5217" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

